reviews.text: We experienced excellent and fast customer service. We really enjoyed the salsa bar and were able to sample various salsas - the pineapple habanero salsa was a must try! Sweet and spicy. The tacos, rice, and beans were fantastic. The beans were the most surprising - full of flavor and properly seasoned, not bland at all. The chicken Milanese tacos were a delight. The atmosphere was cozy and the staff was friendly. I highly recommend checking this hidden gem out if you're in the area.

Chips and amazing collection of salsas to try from the bar!! Both the vegetarian tacos were good - Avocado and Sou chorizo. They tasted even better with the salsas.

Mexican rice was fluffy and tasty. They were out of veggie tamales.

Friendly staff and fast service.

This is definitely a hidden gem! üíé Its very unique with it having its salsa bar, which you have a variety of options to choose from. The decorations and artwork were beautiful to look at. service was amazing and the food was delicious!

The best beef quesibirria tacos i have ever had! Although we did have a little issue with the rice, every taco i ate was wonderful! And my margarita was on point. I definitely will be back soon to try more flavors

Stopped in today with my wife to try this spot was not disappointed! We were greeted instantly and got to choose our seats. The taco selection is great. I ordered a seared shrimp, Baja tilapia, and  fried calamari while my wife ordered a seared shrimp, ribeye, and grilled chicken. All the of tacos were fantastic! We also took advantage of the salsa bar, the cilantro and chipotle were our favorite. Highly recommend each one!  Stop in you won‚Äôt regret it!  If you have room try some of their homemade churros! They are fresh and crispy (not soggy or previously frozen) and served with ice cream. Literally the best churro I have ever had. We will definitely be back !
